lead_paragraph: Axis armies wait in Libya for the signal to attack Egypt. Reinforcements have been reaching them steadily. Despite the combined efforts of the R.A.F. and the British Navy, it is estimated that only about one-fourth of the ships carrying men, machines and munitions from Italy to this outpost of Mussolini's shattered empire have been destroyed.
